The selenium dependency is loading during the Travis CI build, and it looks like my PR and others before it have been failing because `selenium-webdriver 3.4.3` requires Ruby >= 2.0.

I am 100% okay with abandoning this PR if you feel it's unwarranted. I just needed to make these changes to make it work locally. Thanks for your feedback!

If it's helpful for anyone else; until this is complete I've been working around it with an nginx container in my docker-compose setup that rewrites the responses using the following location config:

````
	location /mail {
		proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:40130/;
		proxy_http_version 1.1;
		proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
		proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
		proxy_read_timeout 1d;
		sub_filter 'src="/'     'src="/mail/';
		sub_filter 'href="/'    'href="/mail/';
		sub_filter 'url(/'      'url(/mail/';
		sub_filter '"/messages' '"/mail/messages';
		sub_filter_types text/html text/css application/javascript;
		sub_filter_once off;
	}
````

